{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceProtocol"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns whether "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"source"},{"text":" has been destroyed.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/sourceprotocol\/isdestroyed"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceProtocol\/isDestroyed","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"isDestroyed","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is important when you operate upon your objects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"from within idle handlers, but may have freed the object"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"before the dispatch of your idle handler."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["static gboolean","idle_callback (gpointer data)","{","  SomeWidget *self = data;","   ","  g_mutex_lock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","  \/\/ do stuff with self","  self->idle_id = 0;","  g_mutex_unlock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","   ","  return G_SOURCE_REMOVE;","}"," ","static void","some_widget_do_stuff_later (SomeWidget *self)","{","  g_mutex_lock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","  self->idle_id = g_idle_add (idle_callback, self);","  g_mutex_unlock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","}"," ","static void","some_widget_init (SomeWidget *self)","{","  g_mutex_init (&self->idle_id_mutex);","","  \/\/ ...","}","","static void","some_widget_finalize (GObject *object)","{","  SomeWidget *self = SOME_WIDGET (object);","   ","  if (self->idle_id)","    g_source_remove (self->idle_id);","   ","  g_mutex_clear (&self->idle_id_mutex);","","  G_OBJECT_CLASS (parent_class)->finalize (object);","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will fail in a multi-threaded application if the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"widget is destroyed before the idle handler fires due"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to the use after free in the callback. A solution, to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this particular problem, is to check to if the source"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"has already been destroy within the callback.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["static gboolean","idle_callback (gpointer data)","{","  SomeWidget *self = data;","  ","  g_mutex_lock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","  if (!g_source_is_destroyed (g_main_current_source ()))","    {","      \/\/ do stuff with self","    }","  g_mutex_unlock (&self->idle_id_mutex);","  ","  return FALSE;","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calls to this function from a thread other than the one acquired by the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] the [struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source"},{"text":"] is attached to are typically","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"redundant, as the source could be destroyed immediately after this function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"returns. However, once a source is destroyed it cannot be un-destroyed, so"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this function can be used for opportunistic checks from any thread.","type":"text"}]}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Property","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib14SourceProtocolPAAE11isDestroyedSbvp","symbolKind":"property","extendedModule":"GLib","role":"symbol","title":"isDestroyed","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"isDestroyed","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"}]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Source":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","role":"symbol","title":"Source","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/source","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Source","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Source","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GSource","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data type","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"representing an event source."}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceProtocol/isDestroyed":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Returns whether ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"source"},{"text":" has been destroyed.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourceprotocol\/isdestroyed","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceProtocol\/isDestroyed","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"isDestroyed"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"title":"isDestroyed"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceProtocol":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceProtocol","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSource"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":